  "body": "Ive been using the docs to run through setting up a lodestar node and validators and ill be documenting any gotchyas I find along the way.\r\n\r\n## Install Issues\r\nEnvironment: Digital Ocean - Ubuntu 18\r\nNode: Installed via nvm v12\r\nBugs:\r\n- Creating validator keys does not match the documentation, `$rootDir/validators` doesn't exist, and it seems there are no keys either.\r\n```\r\n> $yarn run cli account wallet create --name primary --passphrase-file ../password.pass \r\nYour wallet's 12-word BIP-39 mnemonic is:\r\n\r\n[redacted]\r\n[removed warning]\r\n\r\nDone in 1.88s.\r\n\r\n> $ tree .lodestar/\r\n.lodestar/\r\n└── wallets\r\n    └── ec35c27f-329d-45ca-b58c-cc4bdb9ad03e\r\n        └── ec35c27f-329d-45ca-b58c-cc4bdb9ad03e\r\n\r\n> $ yarn run cli account validator create --name primary --passphrase-file ../password.pass \r\nDone in 1.95s.\r\n\r\n> $ tree .lodestar/\r\n.lodestar/\r\n├── keystores\r\n├── secrets\r\n└── wallets\r\n    └── ec35c27f-329d-45ca-b58c-cc4bdb9ad03e\r\n        └── ec35c27f-329d-45ca-b58c-cc4bdb9ad03e\r\n\r\n> $ yarn run cli account wallet list\r\nprimary\r\nDone in 1.58s.\r\n\r\n> $ yarn run cli account validator list\r\n\r\nDone in 1.69s.\r\n```\r\n\r\nGotchyas:\r\n- `sudo apt install build-essential` was needed to remove random node-gyp errors\r\n\r\n## Documentation\r\n- The [create wallet](https://chainsafe.github.io/lodestar/usage/key-management/#create-a-wallet) section is a bit confusing, perhaps some clarity around the `--name` flag would be helpful to users. TBH i dont even understand what it is doing\r\n- General confusion around what `$rootDir` means in the wallet section for `lodestar-cli wallet validator create`",
